main event: Multiple UFO sightings were reported in Washington, DC, observed between 17 May, 26 May, and 1 June 1961.
interesting points: Sighting lasted for approximately 30 minutes,The object was described as a vertical cylinder shape with three colored bands rotating counterclockwise,Weather balloon or light reflecting off high, thin overcast was suggested as a possible explanation,The UFO was tracked by both radar and visual observations,Winds were recorded at 240 knots at 70,000 feet during the sightings.
sighted object: A vertical cylinder shape with three colored bands
witness description: Reported observations from radar and visual tracking systems.
